OL,3,CNeed for close Anglo-Irish ties has
OL,4,Cnever been greater, Martin tells
OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,FThe case for forging a close
OL,8,Fpartnership between Ireland and the UK
OL,9,F"has never been greater", Irish
OL,10,Fpremier Micheal Martin has told Sir
OL,11,FKeir Starmer.
OL,13,FThe two leaders have undertaken a
OL,14,Fnumber of engagements in Cork on the
OL,15,Ffirst evening of the UK-Ireland summit.
OL,17,FSir Keir spent the earlier part of the
OL,18,Fday in Belfast before travelling to
OL,19,FCork for the summit, which follows an
OL,20,Finaugural gathering in Liverpool last
OL,21,Fyear.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
