OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773363777
OL,3,CNeed for close Anglo-Irish ties has
OL,4,Cnever been greater, Martin tells
OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,FDuring the meeting in the city centre,
OL,8,Fwith representatives of the energy and
OL,9,Finfrastructure sector, chants from
OL,10,Fdemonstrators outside the building
OL,11,Fcould be heard.
OL,13,FA few dozen protesters were seen in
OL,14,Fthe city centre, some holding Iranian,
OL,15,FPalestinian or Irish flags, to
OL,16,Fcoincide with the summit of British
OL,17,Fand Irish ministers.
OL,19,FThe next event saw the two leaders
OL,20,Fmeet young people taking part in the
OL,21,FUK-Ireland Youth Summit.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
