OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773363777
OL,3,CNeed for close Anglo-Irish ties has
OL,4,Cnever been greater, Martin tells
OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,FSpeaking in Belfast earlier on
OL,8,FThursday, Sir Keir said he had tried
OL,9,Fto "reset" relations between Britain
OL,10,Fand Ireland since becoming Prime
OL,11,FMinister.
OL,13,F"Of course, it doesn't mean that we
OL,14,Fagree on everything, but it means that
OL,15,Fwe positively engage, constructively
OL,16,Fengage, to overcome any challenges,
OL,17,Fbut also take advantage of huge
OL,18,Fopportunities," he told reporters.
OL,26,@qD@DOUqD@JO]uD@AOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773363777
OL,3,CNeed for close Anglo-Irish ties has
OL,4,Cnever been greater, Martin tells
OL,5,CStarmer
OL,7,F"I was determined to reset that
OL,8,Frelationship, I genuinely feel it's in
OL,9,Fa better place, and most people who
OL,10,Ftalk to me about this say it is in a
OL,11,Fbetter place.
OL,13,F"I'm pleased about that, but if you
OL,14,Fare in a better place, you've got to
OL,15,Fkeep working at it."
OL,17,FSir Keir said that while there were
OL,18,Fissues that the governments in London
OL,19,Fand Dublin did not agree on, there
OL,20,Fwere "not as many issues as many
OL,21,Fpeople try to make out".
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUwD@TO]|D@FOU}D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
